  • Method Details

    • put

      void put(K k, V v)
      Inserts a key-value pair into the dictionary. If the key already exists, the associated value is updated.
      Parameters:
      k - the key to insert or update
      v - the value to associate with the key

    • get

      V get(K k)
      Retrieves the value associated with the given key in the dictionary.
      Parameters:
      k - the key for which the associated value needs to be retrieved
      Returns:
      the value associated with the specified key, or null if the key is not found

    • size

      int size()
      Returns the number of elements present.
      Returns:
      the total count of elements.

    • isEmpty

      boolean isEmpty()
      Determines if the collection or data structure is empty.
      Returns:
      true if the collection or data structure contains no elements, false otherwise.

    • containsKey

      boolean containsKey(Object key)
      Checks if the dictionary contains a mapping for the specified key.
      Parameters:
      key - the key to check for existence in the dictionary
      Returns:
      true if the dictionary contains a mapping for the specified key, false otherwise

    • clear

      void clear()
      Removes all elements from the structure, leaving it empty.

    • keySet

      Set<K> keySet()
      Returns a Set view of the keys contained in the dictionary.
      Returns:
      a Set of keys present in the dictionary.
